=== nix binary --help (head -40) ===
Usage: agent-slack [options] [command]

Slack automation CLI for AI agents

Options:
  -V, --version     output the version number
  -h, --help        display help for command

Commands:
  auth              Manage Slack authentication
  message           Read/write Slack messages (token-efficient JSON)
  canvas            Work with Slack canvases
  search            Search Slack messages and files (token-efficient JSON)
  update [options]  Update agent-slack to the latest version
  user              Workspace user directory
  channel           List conversations, create channels, and manage invites
  help [command]    display help for command
